<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-15T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="270" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/364a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-15T17:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1918—5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>6905. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 212. Please repeat the following to <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1">Schmedeman</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>
                                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NF1">Nansen</persName> states that his Government is aware
                                        of the fact that you have copy of proposed draft of
                                        Norwegian agreement. He asks that this draft be submitted to
                                        his Government, and we have not felt that we could refuse
                                        without exciting suspicion on part of Norwegian Government,
                                        although we would have preferred to have first gone over the
                                        draft with <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NF1">Nansen</persName> here. You are accordingly authorized
                                        to acquaint the Norwegian Government with the terms of draft
                                        which <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> furnished you, at the same time
                                        emphasizing that this draft is preliminary and tentative
                                        only and that it will now be made the subject of discussion
                                        with Doctor <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NF1">Nansen</persName>.</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>